  "text": "From Proposition 3 the design of a globally exponentially stable momenta observer follows trivially, and is omitted for brevity. It should be underscored that the resulting observer is much simpler than the I&I observer proposed in [CITATION_1] . This is particularly true for systems that do not satisfy the integrability Assumption 2 in [CITATION_2] , for which it is necessary to use the, rather involved, and high-gain-like technique of I&I with dynamic scaling.",
